A difference and Algarfa and I had the honor together with the BMT CTN to planning this study.

00:01:59.860 --> 00:02:04.100
This was a phase two multi-center trial of anti-B cell maturation antigen.

00:02:04.900 --> 00:02:07.700
This was Ida cell, we call it target CR.

00:02:08.460 --> 00:02:14.940
And the main gist here was based on the study that we did, we knew that patients who did not

00:02:14.940 --> 00:02:19.880
achieve a complete remission on lenalidomide maintenance had a high risk of relapsing over

00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:20.920
the next two years.

00:02:20.920 --> 00:02:23.080
So if you were MRD positive at the,

00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:29.000
12-month mark after transplant on lenalidomide maintenance, your relapse risk was more than 20%

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:30.440
over the next 24 months.

00:02:30.840 --> 00:02:38.260
So the idea was, can we convert somebody who had less than or equal VGPR into a CR or preferably

00:02:38.260 --> 00:02:40.840
MRD negative CR with the use of Ida cell?

00:02:41.620 --> 00:02:46.780
So the study actually required pain lengths to be on maintenance for at least three months to be

00:02:46.780 --> 00:02:49.600
able to declare that they would not achieve a complete remission.

00:02:49.860 --> 00:02:53.060
And then we would collect for Ida cell, we do the lymphodepleting.

00:02:53.060 --> 00:02:56.180
Then chemo, and then we proceed to infusion of Ida cell.

00:02:57.240 --> 00:02:58.920
And these are just basically the baseline.

00:02:58.920 --> 00:03:05.900
We have very high response rates, more than 80% with very high MRD negative negativity rate to 10

00:03:05.900 --> 00:03:08.940
to the minus five and some to 10 to the minus six.

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:14.900
And this is a swimmer's plot, which only, I think we had one patient who progressed before getting

00:03:14.900 --> 00:03:20.060
the cells because they progressed during bridging and the other patient who progressed after

00:03:20.060 --> 00:03:22.980
getting the cells, everybody else remains in a complete remission.

00:03:22.980 --> 00:03:25.160
Everybody else remains without progression.

00:03:25.380 --> 00:03:30.420
Most of them with MRD negative CRs, no late neurotoxicities, no late Parkinson's.

00:03:30.700 --> 00:03:38.860
So if this is one area, and I do think that first question is, is converting an MRD positive PR or

00:03:38.860 --> 00:03:43.160
VGPR to an MRD negative actually change overall outcomes?

00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:46.320
